        "title": "perf: reuse plugin metadata snapshots",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- reuse current/plugin metadata snapshots through a shared resolver across gateway startup, config, model catalog, channel defaults, setup registry, capability, and secret metadata readers\n- remove per-plugin manifest/source/package file watching from the process memo now that plugin changes require reload/restart\n- add regression coverage for immutable metadata memo reuse, workspace-scoped current snapshots, and compatible config current-snapshot reuse\n- document the gateway/plugin metadata performance change in the changelog\n\n## Verification\n\nBehavior addressed: Gateway and control-plane metadata readers can reuse immutable plugin metadata snapshots instead of repeatedly scanning plugin manifests and filesystem metadata on hot paths.\nReal environment tested: Local macOS checkout plus Blacksmith Testbox Linux changed gate.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`; `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/plugin-metadata-snapshot.memo.test.ts src/plugins/setup-registry.runtime.test.ts src/agents/model-catalog.test.ts`; `pnpm build`; `pnpm check:changed`.\nEvidence after fix: autoreview clean with no accepted/actionable findings; focused Vitest passed 4 files / 92 tests; build passed; Blacksmith Testbox `tbx_01ksbdn0ng6m3b6x48x6gxxrhk` passed `pnpm check:changed`.\nObserved result after fix: current and compatible workspace-scoped metadata snapshots stay on the fast path, and changed lanes typecheck/lint/import-cycle guards pass.\nWhat was not tested: full release/package acceptance lanes and live gateway startup profiling were not rerun for this PR.\n",
